      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Bad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The quicktime events seem strangely ambiguous at times, with the game not being overly clear on when and how often to press the A button. This lead to various instances where I was laughed at by the audience because I either didn't hold down the A button long enough or pressed it too many times. A demonstration in a top corner of the screen or better action UI could have perhaps solved these issues.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Even despite the game's short runtime of three hours, the gameplay loop gets quite repetitive. The developers did their best to mix it up where possible, with one example I specifically recall where you are a guest on radio show instead of putting on a theatre performance. However, those efforts only go so far, where it's obvious that the game is more about the story and personality as opposed to the gameplay variety.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
