      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As previously mentioned, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Once Upon a Jester",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has charm coming out the wazoo! It's story may not be the most complex, but the randomness and laidback nature of its jokes and deliveries are absolutely wonderful. And while the game clearly focuses on this wackiness, the gameplay that's centred around it feels tacked on; and yet on the other hand, it works as it's tied into the theatre performances. It's wonderfully clever and will surely put a smile on your face, but it's important to note that you don't boot up this game for the gameplay.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
